embeds.description:
Create a new Statdock via command. Simple presets include: `dateutc`, `timeutc`, `onlinedndidle`, `members`, `users`, `bots`, `channels`, `roles`
Hint: You can create Statdocks using custom text with `create custom`.
Hint: You can find **many** more counters and customization options, such as setting goals and countdowns, on the [__dashboard__](https://statbot.net/me)!

fields.name: Usage
fields.value:
```!statdocks create <preset>
!statdocks create custom [text]<{{counter #}}>[text]``````Key: <required>, [optional]```

fields.name: Examples
fields.value:
```
!statdocks create users
!statdocks create dateUTC
!statdocks create custom
!statdocks create custom Users: {{19}}
!statdocks create custom {{25}} Users Online```

embeds.title: 🎉 Welcome to Statbot!
embeds.description:
Thank you for inviting Statbot to __Serveur dev bot__! Statbot keeps track of your value statistics in almost real-time and allows you to see them in both discord and your [__**new and shiny dashboard**__](https://statbot.net/dashboard/816380067289759784)!

You also now have instant access to many features including the popular ones below!

fields.name: General Info
fields.value:
• My default prefix is `s?`. Type `s?help` for quick list of commands.
• You can read all about using Statbot in our [__**documentation**__](https://docs.statbot.net/docs). The welcome guide will help community and team builders of all skill levels!
• Tracking of messages and voice starts immediately from the time you invite the bot. It takes a few minutes for the data to show in your stats.

fields.name: Statdocks - Channel Counters
fields.value: Statdocks are super customizable channel counters with free custom names! Use `s?statdock setup` to quickly get started, then head to the powerful configurator on your dashboard for infinite customization!

fields.name: Statroles - Auto-Roles using Stats
fields.value: Statroles increase member retention by helping you reward your regular talkers! Statroles give roles based on your settings for message and voice and then **automatically remove them** when members no longer meet your standards! These can be created on your dashboard as well!
